laboratory_examinations.findings: Minimal dependent bibasilar atelectasis; lung bases clear. Normal heart size without pericardial effusion. Spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, and pancreas normal. Large amount of oral contrast remains in the stomach and has not progressed beyond the duodenum. Mild dilatation of central intrahepatic biliary ducts. Common bile duct mildly prominent measuring up to 6 mm. Liver otherwise normal. No free air or free fluid. Multiple small retroperitoneal and mesenteric lymph nodes, none meet CT criteria for pathologic enlargement. Small amount of free fluid in the pelvis. Large fluid-filled appendix with a large appendicolith near the base measuring approximately 1.6 x 0.6 cm. No evidence of perforation or adjacent abscess formation.
